AGI - Sommozzatori and means of firefighters, gums, small boats, equipped pick-ups of civil protection, drones are engaged in <a href="https://www.agi.it/cronaca/news/2024-06-01/ricerche-ragazzi-dispersi-piena-pernatisone-friuli-26602687/" Also present Carabinieri, local police and staff of the Red Cross. Yesterday morning the river returned the bodies of Patrizia Cormos, 20 years old and Bianca Doros, 23 years old.
"Fourth day. They're all here. Don't quit, let's take Cristian home," writes mayor Michele de Sabata on social media. The divers, in particular, are scrutinizing the areas of the Natisone > where, more likely, the twenty-five could have been brought by the current. The places to be searched, between the Roman Bridge and the Leproso Bridge and the locality of Paderno, were identified according to the topographic analyses conducted by experts, taking into account also the points where the first findings were made.
<div </div
&nbsp;
After yesterday's good weather, there has been a worsening of weather. This resulted in a greater flow of water from the Natisone River. In addition, as they were yesterday, they are now more cloudy.
The two factors complicate research to find the body of Cristian Casian Molnar. Also the level of the river, which yesterday had recorded a lowering so much as to make possible the finding of the bodies of the two girls, > one on the crude and the other under a pile of rams, today it has risen determining a situation less favorable in particular for the team of divers already to work in shaping the course of water.&nbsp;
